<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-144] make jmx count/latency stuff actually useful</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-144</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;i just track those since &quot;the beginning of time&quot; it is not very useful for monitoring.  &lt;br/&gt;
(say things are fine for days, then something breaks &amp;#8211; you have to overcome the days of fine-ness in the avg before you can see anything wrong.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;option 1: reset the counters after each request for data.  problem: then i can&apos;t have multiple collectors (which i don&apos;t need atm but might be nice to have).&lt;br/&gt;
option 2: keep the last N data points and compute an average on demand, but that&apos;s more complicated than just doing a += for each op.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;going to go with option 2.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
